@ijJT1yhOu79UAxqQZMNG4Q Per year is a 1/100 (1%) chance. The probability P of one or more floods with return period of T=100 over n=100 yrs is, using the binomial dist:
P=1-(1-1/T)^n
  =1-(0.99)^100
  = 0.63 (63%)
‚ÄòReturn period‚Äô T=100 is the reciprocal of expected frequency (f=1/100=1/T)
